name: integer_i64_one
description: |
  One is a baseline i64 operand for boundary arithmetic. Adding it to the
  maximum overflows, subtracting it from the minimum underflows, and dividing it
  by zero exercises integer divide-by-zero handling.
format: hex
decode-as: i64
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i64"
  - "one"
  - "overflow"
  - "underflow"
  - "division-by-zero"
  - "baseline"
---
01 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 # 1
